description.0: Thor and Kim discover Red in pretty rough shape since losing his powers. The twosome vow to find the rest of the lost gods.
description.1: X-Factor battles Onslaught's minions who are led by a mind-controlled Havok. While they fight valiantly, the team cannot stop the bad guys from putting Onslaught's plans into motion. Plus, Havok is captured by Polaris, and Random is revealed to be a critical key in one of Dark Beast's plans.
description.2: Guest-starring the X-Men! Will Onslaught, the worlds' most powerful psionic entity, claim Franklin Richards as host? You better believe Reed and Sue won't give up their little boy without a fearsome battle!
description.3: The origin of Onslaught revealed! How is it that Professor X became host of this dangerous psychic entity? And how was Magneto involved in the transfer? All is explained through Wolverine's flashbacks, and first-hand narrative, in this Onslaught-centric issue.
description.4: Facing a full-fledged attack from Onslaught, the X-Men call in assistance from the Fantastic Four and Avengers! It's a massive grouping of superheroes that has to be seen to be believed!
description.7: The fall of Asteroid M! Magneto rounds up his Brotherhood in a retaliatory attack against the United States! Should the X-Men fail, there could be nuclear fallout on a global scale!
description.8: Guest-starring X-Man! X-Force attempts to prevent Sinister from using Nate Grey for genetic experimentation. It's Sinister vs. X-Force, with both sides vs. Onslaught! A dizzying battle will ensue!
description.9: Nate Grey seeks refuge with X-Force after Sinister's plans are derailed. But will Nate's new team be able to protect their newest member? X-Man has escaped thus far by the skin of his teeth, but a new battle may be just on the horizon.
description.11: Professor Xavier is Onslaught? Questions will be answered about the X-Men's most insidious villain in this tell-all issue. Is Xavier truly the traitor his team of mutants believes him to be? And who is really behind the devastation of Onslaught?
description.14: Ben is spying on Garon and Devon Lewis when they are attacked by the assassin-for-hire, Delilah! In battle, Ben learns more than he expected about Lewis...
description.15: The Avengers team-up with the X-Men to take down Onslaught. The teams track down Magneto, believing he is at fault. The team discovers that Magneto is now "Joseph", a de-aged and amnesiac version of the X-Men's foe. But why is Rogue fighting the Avengers tooth and nail to protect Joseph? And is this "de-aged Magneto" really the man he claims to be?
description.16: The Cable/Onslaught crossover issue! Far into the future, Cable fights an uphill battle to save the X-Men of the past. But how is the Hulk involved in this saga? And will he and Cable be able to cooperate long enough to stop Onslaught together?
description.17: Amid a background of destruction and rubble, Captain America stands alone holding the American flag for all to see. Ron Garney effortlessly creates a stoic and patriotic image of the star-spangled Avenger that captures the valor and spirit of the hero. No small feat. Cap, we salute you.
description.20: Five millennia before Luke Skywalker was born - and 1,000 years before two young Jedi reawakened a long-dormant evil - the dark power of The Sith held unquestioning rule over the galaxy. For those black-souled, corrupt Jedi, it was a golden age. For the rest of the galaxy, it was a nightmare.
description.22: Dragon Man's loose...and this time, the big purple guy is under the control of Harrow's insidious device. Can a severely outgunned Spider-Man count on his foe Will o' the Wisp to back him up?
description.25: They outnumber him and outgun him. By all rights, Luke Skywalker should be one dead Jedi-in-training, the target of a surprise attack by Jabba's swoop gang. But he's not... and even he isn't certain of the reason!
description.26: A criminal warlord has stolen a vital bit of information, so vital, in fact, that Wedge and Rogue Squadron were going to steal it themselves! Rather than simply steal it, they'll now have to fight for it! Through the heated deserts of Tatooine, in the midst of a gang war sparked by the death of Jabba the Hutt, the Rogue Squadron risk life and limb for the Rebel Alliance!
description.28: A life-changing issue in the saga of Ben Reilly! Jessica, the girl Ben's after, happens to be the daughter of the burglar that shot Uncle Ben…and she HATES Spider-Man! Can Ben show her that the wall-crawler is truly a hero through and through?
description.29: Spider-Man...spider-sized! Ben Reilly wakes up to find himself shrunk down in a child's bedroom, and everything else is not only giant...but wants him dead!
description.30: ONSLAUGHT RISES! The greatest threat mutantkind has ever known is more powerful than ever, and only Cable stands between him and total domination!
description.37: Salem Center has fallen to a horde N'Garai demons! And team leader Cyclops is the sole responder to the distress call!
description.38: Matt Murdock finally meets Spider-Man...wait, what? That's right, Daredevil teams up with the NEW Spider-Man, Ben Reilly, but can they overcome the sinister new menace known only as the Shooter?
description.39: Shadowcat, Nightcrawler and Colossus must confront their alternate-reality counterparts...whipped into existence by Belasco, demon of the underworld!
description.40: The Hulk is back! And he's angrier than ever, having survived a point blank atomic bomb! But someone has come looking for him to ask for his help in saving the future - from the Hulk!
description.41: Tony and War Machine are attacked by Morgan Stark, who means to claim all of the Iron Man armors.
description.42: Hammerhead and Don Fortunato both want Kingpin's former empire, and they'll smash anyone that stands in their way to get it! Can Spidey stop this mafia melee before all of New York gets caught in the crossfire?
description.43: As the city recovers from the flood, the Goblin attacks! Who is this new Goblin and how do they know so much about Miguel? All is revealed in this action-packed issue!
description.44: It is revealed that Yggdrasil is responsible for Thor's power loss! With the help of Doctor Strange, Thor battles to save Asgard! Meanwhile, Amora and the Ice Giants try and capture the Realm Eternal!
description.46: The fate of Franklin Richards decided in this issue! Has Franklin been reunited with his parents as the child he once was? And will one of the youngest members of the FF become a student of Xavier's Institute?
description.47: Are the X-Men prepared for the unstoppable return of the Juggernaut?
description.49: Featuring Juggernaut! Will Professor X's step-brother be the mutant to defeat Onslaught?
description.53: Mimban is like a million other planets in the galaxy-a lot of trees, too much mud, and not much else. But one of Mimban's abandoned temples holds a powerful gem-the Kaiburr crystal-capable of magnifying and clarifying one's perception of the Force. Luke and Leia know it's there-somewhere-and so does Darth Vader. And that makes Mimban a whole lot livelier right now than those other planets!
description.54: The crime and death caused by Jabba the Hutt is nothing compared to the chaos created in the wake of his demise! Jabba's legacy is a cache of stolen Imperial hardware and weapons, hidden somewhere on the desert world of Tatooine. Whoever finds the treasure will have enough firepower to rule the planet -- perhaps even the sector! And that means Rogue Squadron must find it first, or else find it aimed at their heads!
description.55: The grand finale of Doctor Strange, Sorcerer Supreme!
description.58: The ruthless Will o' the Wisp is back, more powerful than before, with his sights set on Spidey!
description.59: Prince Xizor controls the largest merchant fleet in the galaxy-that makes him a valuable asset to the Empire and to the Emperor. And that makes him Darth Vader's hated enemy. As Luke, Leia, and Chewbacca head to Tatooine to rescue Han Solo, they get caught in the crossfire of the galaxy's deadliest rivalry... in the Shadows of the Empire.
description.62: Ben and Peter come ever closer to discovering the mastermind behind the plot against them, but the last thing standing in their way is the power of the Molten Man!
description.63: The new Spider-Man meets the Fantastic Four! The Thing has been stranded in an alternate dimension, and the FF needs Spidey's help to get him back!
description.65: Fallout to Onslaught! The team scrambles to make sense of their changed world following Professor Xavier's dark possession.
description.66: With the Hulk missing, it's time for the She-Hulk to take center stage! And she's already in hot water before long, as her and longtime Hulk ally Doc Samson come face to face with the Molecule Man!
description.67: Tony is caught stealing a Picasso from the MOMA and finds himself in hot water.
description.68: Ben Reilly is still wanted for arson - and the only road to clearing his name is by capturing the true guilty party, the man who thoroughly cleaned his clock: Hobgoblin! Plus, Peter Parker makes a momentous decision!
description.69: The attack from New Atlantis has caused a massive flood that devastates the city! Will Spider-Man be able to save the entire city?
description.70: Thor and the others have been transported to an alternate world where Thor is a menace and Loki's a noble hero!
description.72: Doctor Doom of the future vs. the Fantastic Four of the present! The Inhumans guest-star in this issue of galactic proportion. Who is Doom 2099? And why has his time converged with ours?
description.73: Gambit and Jean infiltrate a top-secret government meeting in the Pentagon.
description.75: The First Full Appearance of Onslaught!  Jean Grey vs. Onslaught! A psychic showdown that no Marvel reader will believe!
description.86: First Appearance of Monica Rambeau of Photon!  A battle of the Captain Marvels! Who will be the victor of the title by the end of this issue? Monica Rambeau or Genis-Vell?
description.87: Captured by Gaunt! Spider-Man is at the mercy of his foes, and only one man can save him: the powerless Peter Parker! But who is the true mastermind behind this attack, and why does he seem so familiar?
description.88: Hawkeye and Masque take down the intruder who managed to infiltrate Avengers Mansion. When the identity of the interloper is revealed, Black Widow discovers he's a dangerous acquaintance! Who is Benedict? And why has he kidnapped Masque?
description.89: Race against time! Can Cable and Domino defeat the sinister Post - before Cable's tehcno-virus takes over for good?
description.92: The residents of Mrlsst should have learned their lesson long ago, when a noble Jedi sacrificed himself that the Empire might leave the Academy unharmed-nobody wins when you play in politics. But old lessons are easily forgotten in the heat of war. Over the years, the Academy has become a snake pit of secrets and plotting, and students and professors fight each other and one another. And now they're about to get a refresher course, the kind that's taught with blood and fire. Unfortunately for Wedge and the Rogue Squadron crew, the lesson comes just as they arrive on Mrlsst.
description.96: Spider-Man's deadly battle with the new Hobgoblin continues! But as the showdown drags on, Ben becomes increasingly cornered! Is this the end of Spider-Man?
description.97: While a grim Luke Skywalker reels from Darth Vader's revelation on the cloud city of Bespin, the tattered remnants of the Rebel fleet desperately seek sanctuary and time to muster new allies. Their forces are weak, and that has not escaped the notice of Emperor Palpatine-ultimate victory lies within his grasp. All it will take is another blow to crush this Rebel Alliance, one more straw to break their backs. A blow, Palpatine reasons, that could be struck by the vast, criminal underworld that lurks within the Shadows of the Empire...
description.98: Ben Reilly - exposed! After a seemingly routine job stopping a robbery, the unthinkable happens - Ben gets snapped by a camera, without a mask! How will he be able to keep his identity a secret now?

6.text: Spidey must rescue an astronaut from Rhino’s rage!

12.text: “Onslaught” tie-in! What is its impact on the next generation of X-Men?

17.text: Captain America is back and he must save Sharon Carter from certain death!

Amid a background of destruction and rubble, Captain America stands alone holding the American flag for all to see.  Ron Garney effortlessly creates a stoic and patriotic image of the star-spangled Avenger that captures the valor and spirit of the hero.  No small feat.  Cap, we salute you.

18.text: Angel Face has escaped, and she wants revenge on the Green Goblin! So why is she heading straight to the Daily Bugle?

19.text: If the symbiote doesn’t eat a brain soon, it’ll eat the big one. Eddie must keep his “other” under control, or else Venom will become a cannibal!

21.text: Electro and the Eel star in a two-for-one special against Spider-Man!

22.text: Dragon Man's loose...and this time, the big purple guy is under the control of Harrow's insidious device. Can a severely outgunned Spider-Man count on his foe Will o' the Wisp to back him up?

23.text: The Avengers receive a prophecy from the future...that spells certain doom for Earth's Mightiest!

24.text: MAN WITHOUT A COUNTRY PART 4 Machinesmith has set a plan in motion that will bring down a S.H.I.E.L.D. helicarrier. Thousands of miles away, Steve Rogers and Sharon Carter attempt to thwart the evil genius' machinations!

27.text: Cyclops and Phoenix's adventure into the past continues! What could the evil Apocalypse want with the seemingly ordinary Dr. Nathaniel Essex? No doubt it's something sinister!

31.text: Phil's powers reach their limit as he attempts to rescue Ricko from the robots of Murderworld!

32.text: With Venom’s back against the wall, he must kill his predator, Xenophage!

33.text: While springing Deadpool from the Weisman Institute, Siryn is plagued by visions of the man she’s trying to rescue. Shatterstar makes a full recovery, while Risque and Warpath explore a burgeoning romance. Can it be that Deadpool belongs in an asylum for the criminally insane? By the end of this issue, you’ll have your answer!

36.text: Vulture hatches a plan to defeat Spider-Man!

42.text: Hammerhead and Don Fortunato both want Kingpin's former empire, and they'll smash anyone that stands in their way to get it! Can Spidey stop this mafia melee before all of New York gets caught in the crossfire?

48.text: Elektra helps Wolverine tame his inner beast by training him in the ways of the warrior!

51.text: Will the X-Cutioner make a clean cut through one of Gen X’s pivotal members?

55.text: The grand finale of Doctor Strange, Sorcerer Supreme!

56.text: MAN WITHOUT A COUNTRY PART 3 Sharon Carter and Steve Rogers are in Moldavia, hunting the man known as Machinesmith. But will Carter's recently returned feelings for Rogers compromise the mission? Find out here!

57.text: Will Spidey conquer Commanda, a brazen jewel thief?

58.text: The ruthless Will o' the Wisp is back, more powerful than before, with his sights set on Spidey!

60.text: Wolverine stars in Slay-per-view, as he fights alongside Marvel's smallest and mightiest- the X-Babies!

61.text: X-Men favorites Cyclops and Phoenix together travel back in time to the year 1859! Here, they discover the true origins of two of their biggest foes…

63.text: The new Spider-Man meets the Fantastic Four! The Thing has been stranded in an alternate dimension, and the FF needs Spidey's help to get him back!

64.text: Matt returns to the Nelson and Murdock law office. But will Foggy request a new partner be thrown in the mix?

68.text: Ben Reilly is still wanted for arson - and the only road to clearing his name is by capturing the true guilty party, the man who thoroughly cleaned his clock: Hobgoblin! Plus, Peter Parker makes a momentous decision!

74.text: Wolverine has gone feral and he’s roaming the streets of New York City! How will the criminals and innocents fare with Logan on the loose? Meanwhile, someone is keeping an eye on Wolverine and you’ll never guess who it is!

77.text: X-Force holds the peacekeeping task force, S.H.I.E.L.D., to task! The crew splits up and starts decimating different parts of the Helicarrier, all in an attempt to recover kidnapped mutant comrades!

79.text: Madelyne Pryor becomes fully entrenched with Selene and her agenda. Holocaust dukes it out with X-Man…and only one will be left standing!

81.text: Nathan takes on the title of Askani’son, after Madame Sanctity announces him to her followers. During the reveling, Aliya pulls Nathan aside and encourages him to re-think his allegiance to Sanctity. She reveals that her teacher has been going mad for some time, and that Sanctity encourages a hive-mind mentality. Nathan now believes that it is Aliya, and not Madame Sanctity, who is destined to become his teacher.

82.text: While under the evil influence, Synch cuts a destructive swathe through the team!

84.text: Jonathan Gatesworth goes after his stolen tech to reclaim what he feels his rightfully his.

85.text: On Venom’s quest to put an end to a serial killer, Brock is led to Donna, a female symbiote. The two battle against their alien predator!

86.text: A battle of the Captain Marvels! Who will be the victor of the title by the end of this issue? Monica Rambeau or Genis-Vell?

90.text: Spider-Man has been captured! Mr. Sinister does his best to make sure the Wall-Crawler is destroyed!

91.text: Spidey swings into action to save a young mutant from Mr. Sinister!

94.text: Peter Parker brings Batwing to Dr. Connors to help cure him...but ends up in a battle with the fearsome Lizard!

95.text: Wolverine verges on the brink of insanity when his animal instincts take over. Wolverine and the X-Men continue to fight the stone creatures that Ozymandias has created. Will Logan find enough control to get his teammates out of harm’s way?

96.text: Spider-Man's deadly battle with the new Hobgoblin continues! But as the showdown drags on, Ben becomes increasingly cornered! Is this the end of Spider-Man?

99.text: Spider-Man - wanted for murder! J. Jonah Jameson is up to his old tricks, offering $100,000 for the scoop behind the dirty deed! Can Spider-Man clear his name in time?
